[2026-03-09T21:12:19Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BwC3jW9U52qS7AfxsmW3Le","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the Cloche codebase. Let me compile my findings into a detailed report.\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE CLOCHE CODEBASE EXPLORATION REPORT\n\nI have thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and understand the complete workflow execution system. Here's the detailed breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. HOST WORKFLOW STRUCTURE (.cloche/host.cloche)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche`\n\nHost workflows run on the host machine (daemon process) and have three types of steps:\n- **script steps** (`run` field) - Execute shell commands\n- **agent steps** (`prompt` field) - Invoke coding agents  \n- **workflow steps** (`workflow_name` field) - Dispatch and wait for container workflows\n\nExample from the codebase:\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step merge {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/merge-to-main.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step cleanup {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/cleanup-run.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt\n  ready-tasks:fail -> abort\n  ... (wiring continues)\n}\n```\n\nKey characteristics:\n- First step defined becomes the entry point\n- Wiring syntax: `step_name:result -> next_step`\n- Terminal targets: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure)\n- Workflow steps dispatch container workflows by name\n\n---\n\n### 2. DAEMON STARTUP AND AUTO-EXECUTION (cmd/cloched/main.go)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\nThe daemon initialization flow:\n\n1. **Load Configuration**\n   - Global config from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n   - Environment variable overrides (CLOCHE_DB, CLOCHE_LISTEN, CLOCHE_IMAGE, etc.)\n\n2. **Initialize Store & Runtime**\n   - SQLite store (`internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n   - Container runtime (Docker or local process execution)\n   - Configurable via environment or config file\n\n3. **Auto-execute Active Projects** (line 107)\n   ```go\n   autoRunActiveProjects(store, srv)\n   ```\n   \n   **findMainWorkflow() function (line 235-260):**\n   - Reads `.cloche/host.cloche` from project directory\n   - Parses it with `dsl.ParseForHost()`\n   - Searches for the first `workflow_name` step\n   - Returns the container workflow name to dispatch\n   - Expects workflow name to be \"main\"\n\n   **autoRunActiveProjects() function (line 200-231):**\n   - Scans all known projects via `store.ListProjects()`\n   - Checks `<projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml` for `active = true`\n   - For each active project:\n     - Calls `findMainWorkflow()` to get container workflow name\n     - Invokes `srv.RunWorkflow()` in a background goroutine\n     - Does NOT block the gRPC server\n\n---\n\n### 3. DOMAIN TYPES (internal/domain/)\n\n**Core Types in `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`:**\n\n```go\ntype WorkflowLocation string\nconst (\n    LocationContainer = \"container\"  // Runs in Docker container\n    LocationHost      = \"host\"       // Runs on host machine\n)\n\ntype StepType string\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    = \"agent\"       // prompt field\n    StepTypeScript   = \"script\"      // run field\n    StepTypeWorkflow = \"workflow\"    // workflow_name field (host only)\n)\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType\n    Results []string           // Declared possible results\n    Config  map[string]string  // Key-value config: prompt, run, workflow_name, etc.\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire             // Step:result -> next_step edges\n    Collects  []Collect          // Fanout/wait conditions\n    EntryStep string             // First step\n    Config    map[string]string  // Workflow-level config\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From   string  // Step name\n    Result string  // Result name\n    To     string  // Next step (or \"done\"/\"abort\")\n}\n\ntype Collect struct {\n    Mode       CollectMode        // \"all\" or \"any\"\n    Conditions []WireCondition    // Multiple (step, result) pairs\n    To         string             // Target when satisfied\n}\n```\n\n**Run State in `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`:**\n\n```go\ntype RunState string\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState\n    ActiveSteps    []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string    // Docker container or local process ID\n    BaseSHA        string    // Git HEAD for result branch creation\n    ContainerKept  bool      // Retain container after completion\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. WORKFLOW DSL PARSING (internal/dsl/)\n\n**Parser in `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`:**\n\nTwo entry points:\n```go\nfunc ParseForHost(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error) {\n    return Parse(input, WithLocation(domain.LocationHost))\n}\n\nfunc ParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error) {\n    return Parse(input, WithLocation(domain.LocationContainer))\n}\n```\n\n**Parsing Flow:**\n1. Lexer tokenizes the DSL (braces, brackets, identifiers, strings)\n2. Parser reads tokens and builds the workflow AST\n3. Step type is **inferred** from content:\n   - If has `prompt` field â†’ StepTypeAgent\n   - If has `run` field â†’ StepTypeScript\n   - If has `workflow_name` field â†’ StepTypeWorkflow\n4. Validation:\n   - All declared results must be wired\n   - All steps must be reachable from entry\n   - No orphaned steps\n   - workflow_name steps only in host workflows (ValidateLocation)\n\n**Lexer in `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go`:**\n- Tokenizes: keywords (workflow, step, collect), operators ({, }, [, ], :, ->, =), strings, identifiers\n- Skips whitespace and comments\n- Tracks line/column for error reporting\n\n---\n\n### 5. CLOCHE-AGENT EXECUTION (cmd/cloche-agent/)\n\n**Entry Point in `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`:**\n\nThe agent runs inside the container with a single argument (workflow file path):\n```go\nworkflowPath := os.Args[1]  // e.g., \".cloche/develop.cloche\"\nrunID := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_RUN_ID\")\n\nrunner := agent.NewRunner(agent.RunnerConfig{\n    WorkflowPath: workflowPath,\n    WorkDir:      workDir,\n    StatusOutput: os.Stdout,\n    RunID:        runID,\n})\n\nerr := runner.Run(ctx)\n```\n\n**Runner Implementation in `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`:**\n\n1. **Parse the workflow** (must be container location):\n   ```go\n   wf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n   ```\n\n2. **Initialize adapters:**\n   - Generic adapter - executes shell commands (`run` steps)\n   - Prompt adapter - executes agent steps (`prompt` steps)\n   - Both write step output to `.cloche/output/<step-name>.log`\n\n3. **Create execution engine** and provide a `stepExecutor`:\n   ```go\n   type stepExecutor struct {\n       workDir   string\n       generic   *generic.Adapter\n       prompt    *prompt.Adapter\n       logStream *logstream.Writer\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Run the engine:**\n   ```go\n   run, runErr := eng.Run(ctx, wf)\n   ```\n\n5. **Write status messages** as JSON lines to stdout:\n   ```json\n   {\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}\n   {\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"result\":\"success\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}\n   {\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}\n   ```\n\n---\n\n### 6. EXECUTION ENGINE (internal/engine/engine.go)\n\n**Core Algorithm:**\n\n```go\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error) {\n    run := domain.NewRun(generateRunID(), wf.Name)\n    run.Start()\n    \n    // 1. Launch entry step\n    launchStep(wf.EntryStep)\n    \n    // 2. Event loop - main execution\n    for activeCount > 0 {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            return run, fmt.Errorf(\"cancelled\")\n        \n        case sr := <-results:\n            activeCount--\n            \n            // Validate result is declared\n            if !isResultDeclared(step, sr.result) {\n                return run, fmt.Errorf(\"undeclared result\")\n            }\n            \n            // Record completion\n            run.RecordStepComplete(sr.stepName, sr.result)\n            \n            // Process wiring\n            nextSteps, wireErr := wf.NextSteps(sr.stepName, sr.result)\n            for _, target := range nextSteps {\n                if target == \"done\" {\n                    doneCount++\n                } else if target == \"abort\" {\n                    aborted = true\n                } else {\n                    launchStep(target)\n                }\n            }\n            \n            // Process collects (fanout wait conditions)\n            for _, cs := range cStates {\n                // Check if collect conditions satisfied\n                if shouldFire {\n                    launchStep(cs.collect.To)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Determine final state\n    if doneCount > 0 {\n        run.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n    } else {\n        run.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Concurrent step execution via goroutines\n- Step timeout support (default 30 minutes)\n- Wiring validates next steps based on (step, result) pairs\n- Collect clauses enable fanout and synchronization\n- Maximum step count limit (default 1000)\n\n---\n\n### 7. RUNWORKFLOW IN DAEMON (internal/adapters/grpc/server.go)\n\n**Entry Point - RunWorkflow RPC (line 79-126):**\n\n```go\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n    // Generate unique run ID\n    runID := domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n    \n    // Create run in store (pending state)\n    run := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\n    run.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\n    s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run)\n    \n    // Launch container start + tracking in background\n    go s.launchAndTrack(runID, image, keepContainer, req)\n    \n    // Return immediately\n    return &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n}\n```\n\n**launchAndTrack (line 131-179):**\n\n1. Ensure container image is built (auto-rebuild if Dockerfile changed)\n2. Record base git SHA from `git rev-parse HEAD`\n3. Start container via runtime:\n   ```go\n   containerID, err := s.container.Start(ctx, ports.ContainerConfig{\n       Image:        image,\n       WorkflowName: req.WorkflowName,\n       ProjectDir:   req.ProjectDir,\n       RunID:        runID,\n   })\n   ```\n4. Call trackRun in background (doesn't block)\n\n**trackRun (line 181-355):**\n\n1. Attach to container stdout\n2. Parse JSON-line status messages from cloche-agent\n3. Record step start/completion events\n4. Extract output files from container\n5. **Extract results to git branch** (line 276-299):\n   - Uses `docker.ExtractResults()` to create worktree\n   - Branch name: `cloche/<runID>`\n   - Based on baseSHA (Git HEAD at start)\n6. Finalize run state based on exit code and reported result\n7. Trigger evolution (self-evolution system)\n8. Clean up container (keep if failed, remove if successful unless --keep-container)\n\n---\n\n### 8. CONTAINER RUNTIME ADAPTERS\n\n**Docker Runtime in `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`:**\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Runtime) Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ports.ContainerConfig) (string, error) {\n    // Default command: cloche-agent .cloche/<workflowName>.cloche\n    containerCmd := []string{\"cloche-agent\", \".cloche/\" + cfg.WorkflowName + \".cloche\"}\n    \n    // docker create ...\n    // - Copy entire project to /workspace/\n    // - Apply overrides from .cloche/overrides/ on top\n    // - Pass CLOCHE_RUN_ID environment variable\n    // - Copy user's ~/.claude auth files\n    // - docker start\n}\n\nfunc (r *Runtime) AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\nfunc (r *Runtime) Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (int, error)\nfunc (r *Runtime) CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\nfunc (r *Runtime) Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n```\n\n**Local Runtime in `/workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go`:**\n\nSimpler implementation for testing/local development:\n- Runs cloche-agent as a local process instead of Docker container\n- Direct stdout pipe attachment\n- File operations directly on project directory\n\n---\n\n### 9. STEP EXECUTORS (internal/adapters/agents/)\n\n**Generic Adapter (script steps) in `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`:**\n\n```go\nfunc (a *Adapter) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (string, error) {\n    cmdStr := step.Config[\"run\"]\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"sh\", \"-c\", cmdStr)\n    cmd.Dir = workDir\n    \n    output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n    \n    // Extract CLOCHE_RESULT: marker from output\n    markerResult, cleanOutput, found := protocol.ExtractResult(output)\n    \n    // Write to log file\n    os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\", step.Name+\".log\"), cleanOutput, 0644)\n    \n    // Return success or fail based on exit code\n    if err != nil { return \"fail\", nil }\n    return \"success\", nil\n}\n```\n\n**Prompt Adapter (agent steps) in `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`:**\n\n```go\nfunc (a *Adapter) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (string, error) {\n    // Check max_attempts - return \"give-up\" if exceeded\n    \n    // Assemble full prompt from multiple sources\n    fullPrompt := assemblePrompt(step, workDir, runID)\n    \n    // Try each command in fallback chain (default: [\"claude\"])\n    for _, command := range a.Commands {\n        result, stdout, err := a.tryCommand(ctx, command, fullPrompt, workDir, step.Name)\n        if err == nil {\n            // Agent completed successfully\n            return result, nil\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // All fallbacks failed\n    return \"fail\", nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. PORTS/INTERFACES (internal/ports/)\n\n**ContainerRuntime Interface:**\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {\n    EnsureImage(ctx context.Context, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n**RunStore Interface:**\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**AgentAdapter Interface:**\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. STATUS PROTOCOL (internal/protocol/)\n\n**Message Flow:**\n\ncloche-agent writes JSON-line status messages to stdout:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"result\":\"success\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"log\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"message\":\"some output\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T...\"}\n```\n\n**Result Extraction (`protocol/result.go`):**\n\nShell commands can emit markers: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<result-name>`\n- Extracted from output and used as the step result\n- Cleaned output saved to log file (without marker)\n- Fallback: exit code determines success/fail\n\n---\n\n### 12. RESULT EXTRACTION TO GIT BRANCH (internal/adapters/docker/extract.go)\n\n**ExtractResults function:**\n\n1. Copy container `/workspace/` to temporary directory\n2. Create git worktree: `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>`\n3. Check out detached HEAD at baseSHA\n4. Copy container workspace into worktree\n5. Create branch `cloche/<runID>`\n6. Git add and commit with cloche author\n7. Clean up worktree\n8. Host workflow merge step can then use this branch\n\n---\n\n### 13. WORKFLOW EXAMPLES\n\n**Example 1: Simple Build (`/workspace/examples/hello-world/build.cloche`):**\n```\nworkflow \"hello-world\" {\n  step init {\n    run = \"echo 'Initializing...' && mkdir -p src dist\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step generate {\n    run = \"echo '<html>...' > src/index.html\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step build {\n    run = \"cp src/index.html dist/\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step verify {\n    run = \"test -f dist/index.html\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  init:success -> generate\n  init:fail -> abort\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n**Example 2: With Fanout (`/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche`):**\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement { ... }\n  step test { ... }\n  step lint { ... }\n  step quality { ... }\n  step fix { ... max_attempts = \"2\" }\n  \n  implement:success -> test\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n  \n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  \n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n  \n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 14. CONFIGURATION\n\n**Project Config (`<projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml`):**\n```toml\nactive = true\nevolution.enabled = true\nevolution.debounce_seconds = 30\nevolution.min_confidence = \"medium\"\n```\n\n**Global Config (`~/.config/cloche/config`):**\n```toml\n[daemon]\nlisten = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\nhttp = \"localhost:8080\"\nimage = \"cloche-agent:latest\"\ndb = \"cloche.db\"\nruntime = \"docker\"\nagent_path = \"\"\nllm_command = \"claude\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### EXECUTION FLOW SUMMARY\n\n1. **Daemon Startup** â†’ Load config â†’ Auto-execute active projects' host workflows\n2. **findMainWorkflow()** â†’ Parse host.cloche â†’ Find first `workflow_name` step\n3. **RunWorkflow RPC** â†’ Create run â†’ Launch container in background\n4. **Container Start** â†’ Copy project â†’ Launch cloche-agent process\n5. **cloche-agent** â†’ Parse container workflow â†’ Create engine â†’ Execute steps\n6. **Engine Loop** â†’ Launch entry step â†’ Await completions â†’ Follow wiring â†’ Repeat\n7. **Step Execution** â†’ Run script or invoke agent â†’ Extract result â†’ Write logs\n8. **Status Messages** â†’ JSON lines to stdout â†’ Daemon parses and records\n9. **Result Extraction** â†’ Copy container to worktree â†’ Create git branch\n10. **Finalize** â†’ Update run state â†’ Clean up container â†’ Trigger evolution\n\n---\n\n### KEY FILES REFERENCE\n\n| Component | Location |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Daemon Main | `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` |\n| Agent Main | `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` |\n| Domain Types | `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` |\n| DSL Parser | `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go` |\n| Execution Engine | `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` |\n| Agent Runner | `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` |\n| gRPC Server | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` |\n| Docker Runtime | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` |\n| Local Runtime | `/workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go` |\n| Generic Adapter | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` |\n| Prompt Adapter | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` |\n| Status Protocol | `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`, `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go` |\n| Result Extraction | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go` |\n| Ports/Interfaces | `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`, `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`, `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: afde07b64623ce490 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 70527\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 75754</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6864ddb-8a62-468e-9371-23940235ec7e","uuid":"18c7a9ac-2925-4c78-9765-0d6223966461","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the codebase to understand:\n\n1. How host.cloche workflow files are structured (find examples in .cloche/ directories or tests)\n2. How cmd/cloched/main.go currently works - especially findMainWorkflow() and autoRunActiveProjects()\n3. How cloche-agent walks the step graph (look in cmd/cloche-agent/ and internal/ for workflow execution logic)\n4. The workflow DSL parsing code (internal/domain/ types like Workflow, Step, Result)\n5. How RunWorkflow() works in the daemon\n6. The ports/adapters for container runtime and agent\n\nRead all relevant files fully. I need to understand the complete picture of workflow execution.","agentId":"afde07b64623ce490","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the Cloche codebase. Let me compile my findings into a detailed report.\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE CLOCHE CODEBASE EXPLORATION REPORT\n\nI have thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and understand the complete workflow execution system. Here's the detailed breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. HOST WORKFLOW STRUCTURE (.cloche/host.cloche)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche`\n\nHost workflows run on the host machine (daemon process) and have three types of steps:\n- **script steps** (`run` field) - Execute shell commands\n- **agent steps** (`prompt` field) - Invoke coding agents  \n- **workflow steps** (`workflow_name` field) - Dispatch and wait for container workflows\n\nExample from the codebase:\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  step ready-tasks {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh 1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step merge {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/merge-to-main.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step cleanup {\n    run = \"bash .cloche/scripts/cleanup-run.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  ready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt\n  ready-tasks:fail -> abort\n  ... (wiring continues)\n}\n```\n\nKey characteristics:\n- First step defined becomes the entry point\n- Wiring syntax: `step_name:result -> next_step`\n- Terminal targets: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure)\n- Workflow steps dispatch container workflows by name\n\n---\n\n### 2. DAEMON STARTUP AND AUTO-EXECUTION (cmd/cloched/main.go)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\nThe daemon initialization flow:\n\n1. **Load Configuration**\n   - Global config from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n   - Environment variable overrides (CLOCHE_DB, CLOCHE_LISTEN, CLOCHE_IMAGE, etc.)\n\n2. **Initialize Store & Runtime**\n   - SQLite store (`internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n   - Container runtime (Docker or local process execution)\n   - Configurable via environment or config file\n\n3. **Auto-execute Active Projects** (line 107)\n   ```go\n   autoRunActiveProjects(store, srv)\n   ```\n   \n   **findMainWorkflow() function (line 235-260):**\n   - Reads `.cloche/host.cloche` from project directory\n   - Parses it with `dsl.ParseForHost()`\n   - Searches for the first `workflow_name` step\n   - Returns the container workflow name to dispatch\n   - Expects workflow name to be \"main\"\n\n   **autoRunActiveProjects() function (line 200-231):**\n   - Scans all known projects via `store.ListProjects()`\n   - Checks `<projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml` for `active = true`\n   - For each active project:\n     - Calls `findMainWorkflow()` to get container workflow name\n     - Invokes `srv.RunWorkflow()` in a background goroutine\n     - Does NOT block the gRPC server\n\n---\n\n### 3. DOMAIN TYPES (internal/domain/)\n\n**Core Types in `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`:**\n\n```go\ntype WorkflowLocation string\nconst (\n    LocationContainer = \"container\"  // Runs in Docker container\n    LocationHost      = \"host\"       // Runs on host machine\n)\n\ntype StepType string\nconst (\n    StepTypeAgent    = \"agent\"       // prompt field\n    StepTypeScript   = \"script\"      // run field\n    StepTypeWorkflow = \"workflow\"    // workflow_name field (host only)\n)\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType\n    Results []string           // Declared possible results\n    Config  map[string]string  // Key-value config: prompt, run, workflow_name, etc.\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire             // Step:result -> next_step edges\n    Collects  []Collect          // Fanout/wait conditions\n    EntryStep string             // First step\n    Config    map[string]string  // Workflow-level config\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From   string  // Step name\n    Result string  // Result name\n    To     string  // Next step (or \"done\"/\"abort\")\n}\n\ntype Collect struct {\n    Mode       CollectMode        // \"all\" or \"any\"\n    Conditions []WireCondition    // Multiple (step, result) pairs\n    To         string             // Target when satisfied\n}\n```\n\n**Run State in `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`:**\n\n```go\ntype RunState string\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState\n    ActiveSteps    []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string    // Docker container or local process ID\n    BaseSHA        string    // Git HEAD for result branch creation\n    ContainerKept  bool      // Retain container after completion\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. WORKFLOW DSL PARSING (internal/dsl/)\n\n**Parser in `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`:**\n\nTwo entry points:\n```go\nfunc ParseForHost(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error) {\n    return Parse(input, WithLocation(domain.LocationHost))\n}\n\nfunc ParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error) {\n    return Parse(input, WithLocation(domain.LocationContainer))\n}\n```\n\n**Parsing Flow:**\n1. Lexer tokenizes the DSL (braces, brackets, identifiers, strings)\n2. Parser reads tokens and builds the workflow AST\n3. Step type is **inferred** from content:\n   - If has `prompt` field â†’ StepTypeAgent\n   - If has `run` field â†’ StepTypeScript\n   - If has `workflow_name` field â†’ StepTypeWorkflow\n4. Validation:\n   - All declared results must be wired\n   - All steps must be reachable from entry\n   - No orphaned steps\n   - workflow_name steps only in host workflows (ValidateLocation)\n\n**Lexer in `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go`:**\n- Tokenizes: keywords (workflow, step, collect), operators ({, }, [, ], :, ->, =), strings, identifiers\n- Skips whitespace and comments\n- Tracks line/column for error reporting\n\n---\n\n### 5. CLOCHE-AGENT EXECUTION (cmd/cloche-agent/)\n\n**Entry Point in `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`:**\n\nThe agent runs inside the container with a single argument (workflow file path):\n```go\nworkflowPath := os.Args[1]  // e.g., \".cloche/develop.cloche\"\nrunID := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_RUN_ID\")\n\nrunner := agent.NewRunner(agent.RunnerConfig{\n    WorkflowPath: workflowPath,\n    WorkDir:      workDir,\n    StatusOutput: os.Stdout,\n    RunID:        runID,\n})\n\nerr := runner.Run(ctx)\n```\n\n**Runner Implementation in `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`:**\n\n1. **Parse the workflow** (must be container location):\n   ```go\n   wf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n   ```\n\n2. **Initialize adapters:**\n   - Generic adapter - executes shell commands (`run` steps)\n   - Prompt adapter - executes agent steps (`prompt` steps)\n   - Both write step output to `.cloche/output/<step-name>.log`\n\n3. **Create execution engine** and provide a `stepExecutor`:\n   ```go\n   type stepExecutor struct {\n       workDir   string\n       generic   *generic.Adapter\n       prompt    *prompt.Adapter\n       logStream *logstream.Writer\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Run the engine:**\n   ```go\n   run, runErr := eng.Run(ctx, wf)\n   ```\n\n5. **Write status messages** as JSON lines to stdout:\n   ```json\n   {\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}\n   {\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"result\":\"success\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}\n   {\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded\",\"timestamp\":\"...\"}\n   ```\n\n---\n\n### 6. EXECUTION ENGINE (internal/engine/engine.go)\n\n**Core Algorithm:**\n\n```go\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error) {\n    run := domain.NewRun(generateRunID(), wf.Name)\n    run.Start()\n    \n    // 1. Launch entry step\n    launchStep(wf.EntryStep)\n    \n    // 2. Event loop - main execution\n    for activeCount > 0 {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            return run, fmt.Errorf(\"cancelled\")\n        \n        case sr := <-results:\n            activeCount--\n            \n            // Validate result is declared\n            if !isResultDeclared(step, sr.result) {\n                return run, fmt.Errorf(\"undeclared result\")\n            }\n            \n            // Record completion\n            run.RecordStepComplete(sr.stepName, sr.result)\n            \n            // Process wiring\n            nextSteps, wireErr := wf.NextSteps(sr.stepName, sr.result)\n            for _, target := range nextSteps {\n                if target == \"done\" {\n                    doneCount++\n                } else if target == \"abort\" {\n                    aborted = true\n                } else {\n                    launchStep(target)\n                }\n            }\n            \n            // Process collects (fanout wait conditions)\n            for _, cs := range cStates {\n                // Check if collect conditions satisfied\n                if shouldFire {\n                    launchStep(cs.collect.To)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Determine final state\n    if doneCount > 0 {\n        run.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n    } else {\n        run.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Concurrent step execution via goroutines\n- Step timeout support (default 30 minutes)\n- Wiring validates next steps based on (step, result) pairs\n- Collect clauses enable fanout and synchronization\n- Maximum step count limit (default 1000)\n\n---\n\n### 7. RUNWORKFLOW IN DAEMON (internal/adapters/grpc/server.go)\n\n**Entry Point - RunWorkflow RPC (line 79-126):**\n\n```go\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n    // Generate unique run ID\n    runID := domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n    \n    // Create run in store (pending state)\n    run := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\n    run.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\n    s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run)\n    \n    // Launch container start + tracking in background\n    go s.launchAndTrack(runID, image, keepContainer, req)\n    \n    // Return immediately\n    return &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n}\n```\n\n**launchAndTrack (line 131-179):**\n\n1. Ensure container image is built (auto-rebuild if Dockerfile changed)\n2. Record base git SHA from `git rev-parse HEAD`\n3. Start container via runtime:\n   ```go\n   containerID, err := s.container.Start(ctx, ports.ContainerConfig{\n       Image:        image,\n       WorkflowName: req.WorkflowName,\n       ProjectDir:   req.ProjectDir,\n       RunID:        runID,\n   })\n   ```\n4. Call trackRun in background (doesn't block)\n\n**trackRun (line 181-355):**\n\n1. Attach to container stdout\n2. Parse JSON-line status messages from cloche-agent\n3. Record step start/completion events\n4. Extract output files from container\n5. **Extract results to git branch** (line 276-299):\n   - Uses `docker.ExtractResults()` to create worktree\n   - Branch name: `cloche/<runID>`\n   - Based on baseSHA (Git HEAD at start)\n6. Finalize run state based on exit code and reported result\n7. Trigger evolution (self-evolution system)\n8. Clean up container (keep if failed, remove if successful unless --keep-container)\n\n---\n\n### 8. CONTAINER RUNTIME ADAPTERS\n\n**Docker Runtime in `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`:**\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Runtime) Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ports.ContainerConfig) (string, error) {\n    // Default command: cloche-agent .cloche/<workflowName>.cloche\n    containerCmd := []string{\"cloche-agent\", \".cloche/\" + cfg.WorkflowName + \".cloche\"}\n    \n    // docker create ...\n    // - Copy entire project to /workspace/\n    // - Apply overrides from .cloche/overrides/ on top\n    // - Pass CLOCHE_RUN_ID environment variable\n    // - Copy user's ~/.claude auth files\n    // - docker start\n}\n\nfunc (r *Runtime) AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\nfunc (r *Runtime) Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (int, error)\nfunc (r *Runtime) CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\nfunc (r *Runtime) Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n```\n\n**Local Runtime in `/workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go`:**\n\nSimpler implementation for testing/local development:\n- Runs cloche-agent as a local process instead of Docker container\n- Direct stdout pipe attachment\n- File operations directly on project directory\n\n---\n\n### 9. STEP EXECUTORS (internal/adapters/agents/)\n\n**Generic Adapter (script steps) in `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`:**\n\n```go\nfunc (a *Adapter) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (string, error) {\n    cmdStr := step.Config[\"run\"]\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"sh\", \"-c\", cmdStr)\n    cmd.Dir = workDir\n    \n    output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n    \n    // Extract CLOCHE_RESULT: marker from output\n    markerResult, cleanOutput, found := protocol.ExtractResult(output)\n    \n    // Write to log file\n    os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\", step.Name+\".log\"), cleanOutput, 0644)\n    \n    // Return success or fail based on exit code\n    if err != nil { return \"fail\", nil }\n    return \"success\", nil\n}\n```\n\n**Prompt Adapter (agent steps) in `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`:**\n\n```go\nfunc (a *Adapter) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (string, error) {\n    // Check max_attempts - return \"give-up\" if exceeded\n    \n    // Assemble full prompt from multiple sources\n    fullPrompt := assemblePrompt(step, workDir, runID)\n    \n    // Try each command in fallback chain (default: [\"claude\"])\n    for _, command := range a.Commands {\n        result, stdout, err := a.tryCommand(ctx, command, fullPrompt, workDir, step.Name)\n        if err == nil {\n            // Agent completed successfully\n            return result, nil\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // All fallbacks failed\n    return \"fail\", nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. PORTS/INTERFACES (internal/ports/)\n\n**ContainerRuntime Interface:**\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {\n    EnsureImage(ctx context.Context, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n**RunStore Interface:**\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**AgentAdapter Interface:**\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. STATUS PROTOCOL (internal/protocol/)\n\n**Message Flow:**\n\ncloche-agent writes JSON-line status messages to stdout:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"result\":\"success\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"log\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"message\":\"some output\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-09T...\"}\n```\n\n**Result Extraction (`protocol/result.go`):**\n\nShell commands can emit markers: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<result-name>`\n- Extracted from output and used as the step result\n- Cleaned output saved to log file (without marker)\n- Fallback: exit code determines success/fail\n\n---\n\n### 12. RESULT EXTRACTION TO GIT BRANCH (internal/adapters/docker/extract.go)\n\n**ExtractResults function:**\n\n1. Copy container `/workspace/` to temporary directory\n2. Create git worktree: `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>`\n3. Check out detached HEAD at baseSHA\n4. Copy container workspace into worktree\n5. Create branch `cloche/<runID>`\n6. Git add and commit with cloche author\n7. Clean up worktree\n8. Host workflow merge step can then use this branch\n\n---\n\n### 13. WORKFLOW EXAMPLES\n\n**Example 1: Simple Build (`/workspace/examples/hello-world/build.cloche`):**\n```\nworkflow \"hello-world\" {\n  step init {\n    run = \"echo 'Initializing...' && mkdir -p src dist\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step generate {\n    run = \"echo '<html>...' > src/index.html\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step build {\n    run = \"cp src/index.html dist/\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step verify {\n    run = \"test -f dist/index.html\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  init:success -> generate\n  init:fail -> abort\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n**Example 2: With Fanout (`/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche`):**\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement { ... }\n  step test { ... }\n  step lint { ... }\n  step quality { ... }\n  step fix { ... max_attempts = \"2\" }\n  \n  implement:success -> test\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n  \n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  \n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n  \n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 14. CONFIGURATION\n\n**Project Config (`<projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml`):**\n```toml\nactive = true\nevolution.enabled = true\nevolution.debounce_seconds = 30\nevolution.min_confidence = \"medium\"\n```\n\n**Global Config (`~/.config/cloche/config`):**\n```toml\n[daemon]\nlisten = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\nhttp = \"localhost:8080\"\nimage = \"cloche-agent:latest\"\ndb = \"cloche.db\"\nruntime = \"docker\"\nagent_path = \"\"\nllm_command = \"claude\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### EXECUTION FLOW SUMMARY\n\n1. **Daemon Startup** â†’ Load config â†’ Auto-execute active projects' host workflows\n2. **findMainWorkflow()** â†’ Parse host.cloche â†’ Find first `workflow_name` step\n3. **RunWorkflow RPC** â†’ Create run â†’ Launch container in background\n4. **Container Start** â†’ Copy project â†’ Launch cloche-agent process\n5. **cloche-agent** â†’ Parse container workflow â†’ Create engine â†’ Execute steps\n6. **Engine Loop** â†’ Launch entry step â†’ Await completions â†’ Follow wiring â†’ Repeat\n7. **Step Execution** â†’ Run script or invoke agent â†’ Extract result â†’ Write logs\n8. **Status Messages** â†’ JSON lines to stdout â†’ Daemon parses and records\n9. **Result Extraction** â†’ Copy container to worktree â†’ Create git branch\n10. **Finalize** â†’ Update run state â†’ Clean up container â†’ Trigger evolution\n\n---\n\n### KEY FILES REFERENCE\n\n| Component | Location |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Daemon Main | `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` |\n| Agent Main | `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` |\n| Domain Types | `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` |\n| DSL Parser | `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go` |\n| Execution Engine | `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` |\n| Agent Runner | `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` |\n| gRPC Server | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` |\n| Docker Runtime | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` |\n| Local Runtime | `/workspace/internal/adapters/local/runtime.go` |\n| Generic Adapter | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` |\n| Prompt Adapter | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` |\n| Status Protocol | `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`, `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go` |\n| Result Extraction | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go` |\n| Ports/Interfaces | `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`, `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`, `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` |"}],"totalDurationMs":75754,"totalTokens":70527,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2089,"cache_read_input_tokens":62413,"output_tokens":6021,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input