[2026-03-09T21:13:29Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MmqEt27qjENr55ZAewbyiW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# CLAUDE.md\n     2â†’\n     3â†’This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n     4â†’\n     5â†’## Project Overview\n     6â†’\n     7â†’Cloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     8â†’environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\n     9â†’tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n    10â†’\n    11â†’**Language:** Go\n    12â†’\n    13â†’**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n    14â†’\n    15â†’## Architecture\n    16â†’\n    17â†’Three binaries from one Go module:\n    18â†’\n    19â†’- **`cloche`** (CLI) â€” Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`.\n    20â†’- **`cloched`** (Daemon) â€” Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Does NOT interpret workflow logic.\n    21â†’- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) â€” Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n    22â†’\n    23â†’Hexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\n    24â†’interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter). Adapters implement\n    25â†’them (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Claude Code).\n    26â†’\n    27â†’```\n    28â†’cmd/\n    29â†’  cloche/           # CLI client\n    30â†’  cloched/          # Daemon\n    31â†’  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\n    32â†’internal/\n    33â†’  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n    34â†’  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, notifier)\n    35â†’  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, sqlite, grpc, agents)\n    36â†’```\n    37â†’\n    38â†’## Workflow DSL\n    39â†’\n    40â†’Steps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\n    41â†’built-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n    42â†’\n    43â†’## Project Layout\n    44â†’\n    45â†’Cloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n    46â†’\n    47â†’```\n    48â†’my-project/\n    49â†’â”śâ”€â”€ .cloche/\n    50â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ develop.cloche      # Workflow definition\n    51â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ Dockerfile           # Container image\n    52â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n    53â†’â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n    54â†’â”‚   â””â”€â”€ <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n    55â†’â”śâ”€â”€ src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\n    56â†’â””â”€â”€ CLAUDE.md\n    57â†’```\n    58â†’\n    59â†’## Container Model\n    60â†’\n    61â†’One container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\n    62â†’container at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\n    63â†’top. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n    64â†’\n    65â†’## Agent Support\n    66â†’\n    67â†’Agent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\n    68â†’Generic (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n    69â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9be06376-5a43-40f9-8380-030cf073c859","uuid":"3f3a060d-2181-436e-8740-0a18a3760ba4","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/CLAUDE.md","content":"# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n## Project Overview\n\nCloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\nenvironments for coding agents, a workflow DSL for linking agentic and script-driven\ntasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n\n**Language:** Go\n\n**Full design:** `docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n\n## Architecture\n\nThree binaries from one Go module:\n\n- **`cloche`** (CLI) â€” Short-lived client. Talks to daemon over gRPC. Subcommands: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`.\n- **`cloched`** (Daemon) â€” Long-running. Manages container lifecycle, collects status, persists state. Does NOT interpret workflow logic.\n- **`cloche-agent`** (In-Container) â€” Autonomous. Parses workflow DSL, walks the graph, executes steps, streams status back to daemon. Runs to completion without human intervention.\n\nHexagonal architecture: domain logic is independent of infrastructure. Ports define\ninterfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter). Adapters implement\nthem (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Claude Code).\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/           # CLI client\n  cloched/          # Daemon\n  cloche-agent/     # In-container entrypoint\ninternal/\n  domain/           # Core types (Workflow, Step, Result, Run)\n  ports/            # Interfaces (store, container, agent, notifier)\n  adapters/         # Implementations (docker, sqlite, grpc, agents)\n```\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nSteps report named results; wiring maps results to next steps. `done` and `abort` are\nbuilt-in terminals. See `docs/workflows.md` for syntax and semantics.\n\n## Project Layout\n\nCloche-specific files live in `.cloche/` at the project root:\n\n```\nmy-project/\nâ”śâ”€â”€ .cloche/\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ develop.cloche      # Workflow definition\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ Dockerfile           # Container image\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\nâ”śâ”€â”€ src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)\nâ””â”€â”€ CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n## Container Model\n\nOne container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\ncontainer at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\ntop. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n\n## Agent Support\n\nAgent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\nGeneric (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n","numLines":69,"startLine":1,"totalLines":69}}}
