n```\n\n## Container Model\n\nOne container per workflow run (not per step). The entire project root is copied into the\ncontainer at `/workspace/`, then override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on\ntop. Results are extracted to git branches. Network is allowlisted.\n\n## Agent Support\n\nAgent-agnostic. The `AgentAdapter` interface wraps any coding agent. Initial adapters:\nGeneric (arbitrary commands) and Claude Code.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":48,"oldLines":9,"newStart":48,"newLines":11,"lines":[" ```"," my-project/"," â”śâ”€â”€ .cloche/","-â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ develop.cloche      # Workflow definition","+â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ develop.cloche      # Container workflow definition","+â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ host.cloche          # Host orchestration workflow (runs on host)"," â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ Dockerfile           # Container image"," â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps","+â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ scripts/             # Host-side scripts (e.g. prepare-prompt.sh)"," â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container"," â”‚   â””â”€â”€ <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)"," â”śâ”€â”€ src/                     # Existing project source (untouched)"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
